      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course, I can help you with that. Below is the `solve_vrp` function:\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef solve_vrp(distance_matrix):\n    n = len(distance_matrix)\n    visited = [False] * n\n    current_node = 0\n    total_distance = 0\n\n    for _ in range(n):\n        visited[current_node] = True\n        next_node = -1\n        min_distance = float('inf')\n        for j in range(n):\n            if not visited[j] and distance_matrix[current_node][j] < min_distance:\n                min_distance = distance_matrix[current_node][j]\n                next_node = j\n        \n        total_distance += min_distance\n        current_node = next_node\n\n    total_distance += distance_matrix[current_node][0]\n    return total_distance\n```\n\nThe function starts at node 0 and iteratively visits the nearest unvisited node, adding the distance to the total distance. Finally, it adds the distance required to return back to the start node. It should match the behavior of the tests you provided. Let me know if you need further adjustments!",
